comment._content: Commonwealth War Graves Commission has following details WILLIAMSON, JOHN NEWTON Rank:Private Service No:18826 Date of Death :01/07/1916 Regiment/Service:King's Own Yorkshire Light Infantry 8th Bn. Panel Reference Pier and Face 11 C and 12 A.Memorial THIEPVAL MEMORIAL can be found here www.cwgc.org/search-for-war-dead/casualty/822357/WILLIAMS...

comment.author: 64288588@N05
comment._content: Born circa 1897 in Easingwold, Yorkshire, he was the son of William and Jane Williamson. At the time of the 1911 census he was living with his parents on Long Street, Easingwold. His father was a Joiner/Builder.
